summary:
I remember choosing the bachelor study Human Resources Management (HRM) because of the idea of getting the best out of both employer and employee. To make sure that employees stay motivated and satisfied while they do what is best for the employer and to ensure the employer is a good employer. 

Data is key to make this happen. This is the reason for my interest in HRIS. The combination of data and the right processes can mean so much for employer and employee. In the last years I helped companies improving their internal HR related processes and giving business insights via reports and dashboards. 

Are you interested to hear more about me and my way of working? Feel free to reach out!
